Hello! I recently started programming and came upon an issue that keeps happening every time I try to press enable on FRC Driver Station. What keeps happening is when I first press enable after deploying my code to the robot it like does a little jitter (the robot) or just doesn’t work at all until I press disable and enable again. Can anybody help me with this?
Here is what my FRC Driver Station and LabView code looks like:

Screenshot (2)1276×289 54.6 KB

I’d also like to mention that when this was happening the communications and robot code in the FRC Driver Station was green.
Thank you for all your help!

There are a few code issues that will cause your code to build and deploy, but the second you enable the robot will shut down. When the code crashes, look at the stacktrace in WPIlib and see what the issue is. The most common I come across is a nullPointerException, which doesn’t cause errors until you enable your robot.

If this is in Auto, then I expect it is something simple in code.
If you post your Autonomous Independent.vi it’ll be easy for us to help.

For instance, the motor safety must be handled or disabled during auto, otherwise it swiftly (100 ms) shuts down your motor outputs and you just see the robot twitch.
